{
  "ref": "kaal-xil-dar",
  "categoryRef": "npc",
  "title": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
  "sections": [
    {
      "title": "Before The Ascent of Arceuus",
      "sections": [],
      "dialogues": [
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
              "text": "Human."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
              "text": "Leave us."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "Your presence is not desired."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "How friendly."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "During The Ascent of Arceuus",
      "sections": [
        {
          "title": "First encounter",
          "sections": [],
          "dialogues": [
            {
              "lines": [
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
                  "text": "Human."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
                  "text": "Leave us."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
                  "text": "Your presence is not desired."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Player",
                  "text": "But I need your help! I was sent by Asteros Arceuus, son of Lord Trobin Arceuus."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
                  "text": "Arceuus."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
                  "text": "We know that name."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
                  "text": "The name of a liar."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Player",
                  "text": "Liar?"
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
                  "text": "They came to us. Two of them."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
                  "text": "The brother and the husband."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
                  "text": "Her time was running out. They wanted to give her more."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
                  "text": "We granted them knowledge. To give her more time."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
                  "text": "But they misused it. And the world suffered."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Player",
                  "text": "This knowledge? You mean immortality?"
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
                  "text": "In a way. But it was not meant for that."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
                  "text": "Time was what it was meant for. But time still runs out."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
                  "text": "They put an end to time. They endangered the balance."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Player",
                  "text": "What balance?"
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
                  "text": "For every death, there must be life."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
                  "text": "For every life, there must be death."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
                  "text": "Perfectly balanced."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
                  "text": "As all things should be."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
                  "text": "We serve this balance."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
                  "text": "For without balance, the world burns."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Player",
                  "text": "You're very confusing, you know that right?"
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
                  "text": "Perhaps."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
                  "text": "Perhaps our knowledge is beyond your understanding."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Player",
                  "text": "Well thankfully I didn't come here for knowledge. I came here for help. The Dark Altar is failing and the people of Arceuus are in danger. I need you to help me find the cause."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
                  "text": "The people of Arceuus have had their time."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
                  "text": "This will restore balance."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
                  "text": "Why should we help them?"
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Player",
                  "text": "*sigh* It can never be easy can it."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Player",
                  "text": "Fine. If you help me save the people of Arceuus, then I will help you."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
                  "text": "You assume we need help."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Player",
                  "text": "I've done this enough times to know that everyone wants something, even the masters of life and death."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
                  "text": "Interesting. Maybe the human is not as stupid as it looks."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Player",
                  "text": "Well I've been known to have my moments."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
                  "text": "Very well human."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
                  "text": "We admit, the Arceuus people do have their uses."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
                  "text": "Their work with souls has been useful in helping to maintain the balance."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
                  "text": "We will help them. But first, you will serve us."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Player",
                  "text": "Excellent. What do you need from me?"
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
                  "text": "To the south lies a battlefront."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
                  "text": "There is a grave there. Within it lies a soul, trapped inside a corpse."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
                  "text": "Free this soul. In return, we will provide our help."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Player",
                  "text": "So you just want me to kill a zombie?"
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
                  "text": "A zombie is soulless. An empty shell, reanimated by magic."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
                  "text": "This is a soul. Trapped in this world, when it should have long departed."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
                  "text": "Its existence is an affront to the balance."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Player",
                  "text": "Seems pretty simple."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
                  "text": "Which is why it falls to you."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
                  "text": "Consider it a test."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
                  "text": "If you pass."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
                  "text": "We may have further use for you."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Player",
                  "text": "Hmmm. Very well, I'll go and free this soul."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "title": "After freeing the soul",
          "sections": [],
          "dialogues": [
            {
              "lines": [
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
                  "text": "The human returns."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Player",
                  "text": "I've dealt with the trapped soul."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
                  "text": "You have done well."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
                  "text": "The balance has been restored."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
                  "text": "And now we shall help you."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
                  "text": "While you were busy, so were we."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
                  "text": "We have found the cause of your problem."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Player",
                  "text": "What is it?"
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
                  "text": "You said the Altar was failing."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
                  "text": "This is not correct."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
                  "text": "The Altar is fine, but its power has been redirected."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Player",
                  "text": "Redirected where?"
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
                  "text": "To a construct built by a mortal."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
                  "text": "Right next to the Altar."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
                  "text": "Find it. Destroy it."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
                  "text": "And Arceuus will be saved."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Player",
                  "text": "So I just have to go to the Dark Altar, find this device and then destroy it. Sounds easy enough."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
                  "text": "Then you have what you need."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
                  "text": "You can leave us."
                },
                {
                  "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
                  "text": "Go and save your people."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "dialogues": []
    },
    {
      "title": "After The Ascent of Arceuus",
      "sections": [],
      "dialogues": [
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "The human returns."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "Tell me about yourselves."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
              "text": "We are the Tasakaal."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "We serve the balance."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
              "text": "Between life."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "And death."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "Balance? So you serve Guthix?"
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
              "text": "A pretender."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "We serve another power."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
              "text": "A higher power."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "What power?"
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "One beyond your understanding."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "Why do you serve this power?"
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
              "text": "The anima of this world, it is fed by life."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "Without life, there is no anima."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
              "text": "But life can also destroy. It can endanger the anima."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
              "text": "So life must be kept in check."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "This is our purpose."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "And you were given this purpose?"
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
              "text": "Yes."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "And no."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
              "text": "Our purpose was to wait. But we saw the world burn."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
              "text": "We could not stand by and watch."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "So we left our people. Left our home."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
              "text": "And took on a new purpose."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "I'm still not sure I understand."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
              "text": "Maybe you never will."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "Why did that soul need freeing?"
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
              "text": "Upon death, a soul should leave this world."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "And move to the one beyond."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
              "text": "This soul remained."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
              "text": "It endangered the balance."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "Was it always there?"
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "No."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
              "text": "The body was of one who died a long time ago."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
              "text": "But the soul was of one who died more recently."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
              "text": "It possessed this body."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "We know not why."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "Is this something that often happens?"
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
              "text": "No."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "It is a concerning occurrence."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
              "text": "We believe a mortal to be involved."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
              "text": "Meddling."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "Where one should not meddle."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "Interesting..."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "You said you might have further use for me?"
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
              "text": "We did."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "What did you mean by that?"
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
              "text": "The task you performed."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
              "text": "It was a menial one."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "Another could have filled your role."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
              "text": "But you showed promise."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "So we tested you."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
              "text": "You passed."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "You said it was an important task. Now you say it's a menial one. Which is it?"
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "An important task can still be menial."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
              "text": "There is no contradiction here."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "Hmmm... If you say so."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "So why was it only a small task? Surely saving the Arceuus people was worth more than that."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
              "text": "You assume it was a trade."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "You assume wrong."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "But you said I had to do it to save them?"
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
              "text": "Incorrect."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "We had already committed to saving Arceuus."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
              "text": "But we needed time to determine the problem."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "While we worked, you needed purpose."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
              "text": "So we gave you one."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "I feel a little bit used."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
              "text": "Then you should have paid more attention."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "So what is the further use you have for me?"
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
              "text": "None."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
              "text": "For now."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "But we will call on you again."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
              "text": "That, we can guarantee."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "Why do you hate Lord Arceuus?"
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
              "text": "We granted them knowledge."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
              "text": "For a specific purpose."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "But they misused it."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "Them? Who else was there?"
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
              "text": "Another."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "Another?"
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "Another."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "I can see we're not going to get anywhere here."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "Goodbye."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "Farewell human."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "After A Kingdom Divided",
      "sections": [],
      "dialogues": [
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
              "text": "The human returns."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "What do you know of Xeric?"
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
              "text": "That name."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
              "text": "It is not welcome here."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "Right... sorry. What was it you called him? The great betrayer?"
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "An apt description."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "But why? What did he do?"
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
              "text": "Threatened the balance."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "Plenty of people threaten the balance. Why was he especially bad?"
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "It is not your concern."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "What are you hiding? You call him a betrayer... Did he betray you? Did you work with him?"
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
              "text": "It is not your concern."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "Do you know anything about this rogue Pyromancer?"
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
              "text": "No."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "They are one of many."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
              "text": "We can't determine which one."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "So you know nothing of them?"
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "They have a great strength."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
              "text": "More than many of the others."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "They sound dangerous. What do you plan to do?"
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
              "text": "Nothing."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "Nothing?"
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
              "text": "The Doors of Dinh are safe."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
              "text": "They can do no more harm."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Player",
              "text": "But whoever they are, they're working with Xamphur. Many lives could be at risk."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "Lives are always at risk."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Xil-Dar",
              "text": "But the balance is what matters."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Ket-Jor",
              "text": "Until it is threatened."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "Kaal-Mej-San",
              "text": "There is no need for action."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}